    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. **Add Code:** Add two conditionals to the `check_square(painter)` function definition:\r\n   - First, check if the painter `is_on_paint()`, and if it is, then the painter should `scrape_paint()`.\r\n   - Second, check if the painter `can_move()`, and if it can, then the painter should `move()`. \r\n2. **Run and Test:** Call the `check_square(painter)` function after the `turn_around()` function call. <br>\r\n3. **Discuss:** What can you use to continue to call the `check_square(painter)` function repeatedly so that the painter scrapes up the line of paint it just put down like the image below? <br>\r\n4. **Test and Run:** Give your ideas a try!\r\n   - **Discuss:** How do `if` statements and `while` loops work together in this program? What would happen if we moved the conditionals outside the loop?\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/143dc2209f3ac15665dc9b11545bfb46-image-1738551358664.gif\" style=\"width: 200px;\">",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# create painter object\nfatima = Painter()\n\n# Function defintion to collect paint, move and paint while can move\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef paint_and_move(painter):\n  while painter.is_on_bucket():\n    painter.take_paint()\n  while painter.can_move():\n    painter.move() \n    painter.paint(\"yellow\")\n\n# Function defintion to scrape paint if painter is on paint and move if painter can move\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef check_square(painter):\n  #ADD CONDITIONALS HERE\n\n  \n\n# Function definition to turn around\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef turn_around(painter):\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n  \n# Function Calls\npaint_and_move(fatima)\nturn_around(fatima)\n#ADD CALL TO check_scquare(painter) FUNCTION HERE\n\n  \n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
